body:
Thanks for taking the time to report this.
The test can pass on VCS, but Verilator reports an error.


```
module test_fscanf;
    int cfg_file, f_stat;
    reg[8*8:1] fname;
    int index,count;

    initial begin
        cfg_file = $fopen("cfg.txt", "r");
        f_stat = $fscanf(cfg_file, "%s", fname);
        f_stat = $fscanf(cfg_file, "%d", index);
        f_stat = $fscanf(cfg_file, "%d", count);

        //eof
        f_stat = $fscanf(cfg_file, "%s", fname);
        if(f_stat == -1) begin
            $display("EOF");
        end
        else begin
            $error("Not EOF");
            $stop;
        end

    end
endmodule
```
cfg.txt
```
vec 6163 16
```


What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?
verilator --cc --binary test_fscanf.sv

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
Verilator 5.035 devel master(20250324)

What OS and distribution are you using?
rockylinux9
